Practice problems

  • It’s a good idea to work through these on your own, but if you get very stuck, solutions can be found here

  • All Q and pg references are for Izhikevich (2006):

    Izhikevich, E. M. (2006). Dynamical Systems in Neuroscience: The Geometry of Excitability and Bursting. The MIT Press.

    https://www.izhikevich.org/publications/dsn.pdf

1. Q11 pg 322

All membrane potential responses in the following figure were obtained using an Izhikevich model neuron. Experiment with the model and reproduce the figure.

Electronic version of this figure and reproduction permissions are freely available at www.izhikevich.com

2. Q3 pg 321

Show that when \(b > 0\) the period of oscillations in the quadratic integrate-and-fire model is:

\[ T = \frac{1}{\sqrt{b}} \bigg( \text{atan}(\frac{v_{\text{peak}}}{\sqrt{b}}) -\text{atan}(\frac{v_{\text{reset}}}{\sqrt{b}}) \bigg) \]

3. Q4 pg 322

Show that when \(b < 0\) and \(v_\text{reset} > \sqrt{|b|}\) the period of oscillations in the quadratic integrate-and-fire model with \(v_{peak} = 1\) is:

\[ T = \frac{1}{2 \sqrt{|b|}} \bigg( \text{ln}(\frac{1 - \sqrt{|b|}}{1 + \sqrt{|b|}}) -\text{ln}(\frac{v_{\text{reset}} - \sqrt{|b|}}{v_{\text{reset}} + \sqrt{|b|}}) \bigg) \]

4. Q9 pg 322

When is the following model equivalent to the integrate-and-fire model? \[ \frac{dv}{dt} = I - v - u \\ \frac{du}{dt} = a (b v - u) \\ \text{if } v = 1, \text{then } v \leftarrow 0, u \leftarrow u + d \]

Create any non-trivial input (e.g., use something like a square pulse of current that is strong enough to elicit interesting spiking behaviour from the model), and pass that input to both the above model and also to an integrate and fire neuron. We ought to be able to demonstrate that they respond to this input in the same way, provided some constraints are met.
